Just sitting here trying to come up with a New Year's resolution... having difficulty... can't think of anything that I've done wrong.  I could resolve to try and not be too modest...<br>
Anyway, an intense review of my perfection, in comparison to my non-helicopter pilot, enlisted, grunt, Jarhead, airhead, chicken phobic brothers, led me to contemplate a different theme.  &quot;New Year's Revolutions... after all, they are often revolting in their failures to provide me the proper respect.  The revulsions, generated by their poor typing abilities and spelling, alone, is almost enough to document their rebellion against propriety.  Their collective failure to salute my autographed picture with greater alacrity implies rebellion, mutiny, and insurrection.<br>
Still, I love them... therefore, I have decided to offer them recourse...they can make New Year's revolutions regarding their revolting behavior.<br><br>
My New Year's Revolutions are two in number:<br>
     Try and be more modest!<br>
     Try and not be shocked or repelled by their gluttonous focus on Spam, Peaches and Pound Cake.<br>
     Try and ignor their frequent renouncements and disavowed allegiance to Helicopter Pilots.<br><br>
HAPPY NEW YEAR TO MY REVOLTING BROTHERS OF CHOICE!<br><br>
